claim.claim-text:
1. A method for operating a user equipment (UE) device as part of a wireless network including a first base station and a second base station, the method comprising:
receiving two or more subchannel data streams through two or more respective subchannels of a first MIMO channel between the first base station and the UE device, wherein the first base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the second base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the UE device includes two or more spatially separated UE antennas;
sending to the first base station indicators of signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel;
sending to the second base station indicators of signal quality of two or more subchannels of a second MIMO channel, wherein the second MIMO channel is a MIMO channel between the second base station and the UE device, wherein the wireless network stops transmitting via a given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmitting via a given subchannel of the second MIMO channel in response to a determination that the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel has better signal quality than the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel;
after the wireless network stops transmission via the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmission via the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, performing operations including:
(a) receiving a subset of the two or more subchannel data streams via a subset of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel, wherein the subset does not include the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel; and
(b) receiving at least one new subchannel data stream from the second base station using at least the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, wherein (a) and (b) are performed simultaneously.

4. The method of claim 1, further comprising:
determining the signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel based on pilot signals included in transmissions on the first MIMO channel by the first base station;
determining the signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the second MIMO channel based on pilot signals included in transmissions on the second MIMO channel by the second base station.

8. A user equipment (UE) device for operation as part of a wireless network including a first base station and a second base station, the UE device comprising:
circuitry configured to:
receive two or more subchannel data streams through two or more respective subchannels of a first MIMO channel between the first base station and the UE device, wherein the first base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the second base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the UE device includes two or more spatially separated UE antennas;
send to the first base station indicators of signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel;
send to the second base station indicators of signal quality of two or more subchannels of a second MIMO channel, wherein the second MIMO channel is a MIMO channel between the second base station and the UE device, wherein the wireless network stops transmitting via a given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmitting via a given subchannel of the second MIMO channel in response to a determination that the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel has better signal quality than the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel;
after the wireless network stops transmission via the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmission via the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, perform operations including: (a) receiving a subset of the two or more subchannel data streams via a subset of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel, wherein the subset does not include the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel; and (b) receiving at least one new subchannel data stream from the second base station using at least the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, wherein (a) and (b) are performed simultaneously.

9. The UE device of claim 8, wherein the circuitry is further configured to:
determine the signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel based on pilot signals included in transmissions on the first MIMO channel by the first base station;
determine the signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the second MIMO channel based on pilot signals included in transmissions on the second MIMO channel by the second base station.

11. A non-transitory computer-readable memory medium storing program instructions for operating a user equipment (UE) device as part of a wireless network including a first base station and a second base station, wherein the program instructions, when executed by the processor, cause the processor to:
receive two or more subchannel data streams through two or more respective subchannels of a first MIMO channel between the first base station and the UE device, wherein the first base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the second base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the UE device includes two or more spatially separated UE antennas;
send to the first base station indicators of signal quality of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel;
send to the second base station indicators of signal quality of two or more subchannels of a second MIMO channel, wherein the second MIMO channel is a MIMO channel between the second base station and the UE device, wherein the wireless network stops transmitting via a given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmitting via a given subchannel of the second MIMO channel in response to a determination that the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel has better signal quality than the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel;
after the wireless network stops transmission via the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmission via the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, perform operations including: (a) receiving a subset of the two or more subchannel data streams via a subset of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel, wherein the subset does not include the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel; and (b) receiving at least one new subchannel data stream from the second base station using at least the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, wherein (a) and (b) are performed simultaneously.

14. A method for operating a user equipment (UE) device as part of a wireless network including a first base station and a second base station, the method comprising:
receiving two or more subchannel data streams on two or more respective subchannels of a first MIMO channel between the first base station and the UE device, wherein the first base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the second base station includes two or more spatially separated base station antennas, wherein the UE device includes two or more spatially separated UE antennas;
determining that signal quality of a given one of the two or more subchannels of a second MIMO channel is better than signal quality of a given subchannel of the first MIMO channel between the first base station and the UE device;
sending a message to the first base station requesting the first base station to stop transmitting to the UE device via the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel;
sending a message to the second base station requesting the second base station to start transmitting to the UE device via the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel;
after the wireless network stops transmission via the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel and starts transmission via the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, performing operations including:
(a) receiving a subset of the two or more subchannel data streams via a subset of the two or more subchannels of the first MIMO channel, wherein the subset does not include the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel; and
(b) receiving at least one new subchannel data stream from the second base station using at least the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel, wherein (a) and (b) are performed simultaneously.

17. The method of claim 14, further comprising:
determining the signal quality of the given subchannel of the first MIMO channel based on pilot signals included in transmissions by the first base station;
determining the signal quality of the given subchannel of the second MIMO channel based on pilot signals included in transmissions by the second base station.

